Description: Fragment of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Oval handle to sharp turn. Rectangular stamp. Clay near fine pink-buff; pink core; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Petrie drew three such stamps (Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 52, 5, 53, 2 and 121, 3). Name Aphrodisios.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1229)
